Police officers from Mayville SAPS conducted an operation which yielded positive results in their policing area when they arrested three men with suspected stolen property including copper cables and tools, on Thursday. Police spokesperson, Colonel Thembeka Mbele, said: “Police approached a bakkie with three occupants in Manor Gardens and a search was conducted. Copper cables, three reflector jackets and various tools which included a sledgehammer, chainsaw, iron saw as well as block machine chains were recovered inside the bakkie. Suspects were immediately arrested and were taken to Mayville police station for processing. The three men are aged between 29 and 42. They were charged for being in possession of suspected stolen property. They are expected to appear at the Durban Magistrates Court today.” “Their vehicle was seized and impounded for further investigation. The cables were positively identified by Telkom officials. The suspects will be profiled to ascertain if they can be linked to other cable theft cases,” Col Mbele added. The Provincial Commissioner in KwaZulu-Natal, Lieutenant General Khombinkosi Jula welcomed the arrests and recovery of the stolen property.